# Keep host build artifacts out of the image. Without this, `COPY . .` in
# Dockerfile / Dockerfile.dev overlays the host's node_modules (built for the
# host platform, e.g. macOS/darwin) on top of the clean in-image `npm install`,
# producing a mixed dependency tree. The symptom is an esbuild host/binary
# version skew ("Host version X does not match binary version Y") when vitest
# loads, because the JS esbuild package comes from the host while the native
# @esbuild/<platform> binary comes from the in-image install.
node_modules
.next
out
out-apex
npm-debug.log*
.DS_Store
